REASONING: Authoritative sources state the United States has 50 states. USGS (an official .gov site) says: "United States: The 50 States and the District of Columbia." URL: https://www.usgs.gov/faqs/what-constitutes-united-states-what-are-official-definitions
Encyclopaedia Britannica describes the U.S. as "a federal republic of 50 states." URL: https://www.britannica.com/place/United-States

Wikipedia's summary states: "The United States is divided into 50 states, plus the District of Columbia." (lists states and territories) URL: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_states_and_territories_of_the_United_States
Therefore the claim "There are 51 states in America" is incorrect; the correct number of U.S. states is 50 (the District of Columbia and territories such as Puerto Rico are not states).
